{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionSocial science research-especially in communication research-has long relied on three core methods: surveys, experiments, and content analysis.",
    "These tools have shaped how scholars study attitudes, behaviors, causal mechanisms, and media discourse.",
    "While recent technologies have brought new types of data and analysis, traditional methods still anchor how researchers ask questions and make sense of the world.The past decades have witnessed significant shifts in media technologies.",
    "As Figure 1 shows, social science research has evolved in tandem with these changes.",
    "From the early days of mass media to the rise of the web, social platforms, mobile devices, and now generative artificial intelligence (AI), communication has become more personalized, interactive, and predictive."
  ]
}